The African Rainbow Foundation is hosting a virtual media conference. This as the Motsepe Foundation has pledged R1 billion to fight coronavirus. The Motsepe Foundation has outlined various efforts it’s engaging in to assist South Africa in fighting the coronavirus pandemic. South Africa has 1170 COVID-19 cases and one death. There are nearly 600 000 COVID-19 cases across the globe and over 27 000 deaths. The Motsepe Foundation joins other South African business bodies and lobby groups – who have pledged to work with the government in the fight against the pandemic. Live stream below: